## 1.01 truffle vscode and remix

1. Install VSCode
- Download from https://code.visualstudio.com/

2. Open 1.01-truffle-vscode-remix with VSCode then open terminal

3. Install node
- Install nvm https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm
- Install nodejs using nvm
$ curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.0/install.sh | bash
$ nvm install v14.17.6
$ nvm use v14.17.6
$ node -v
$ v14.17.6

- To make sure that all workshop is the same as in the video, make sure to use node v14.17.6
$ node -v
v14.17.6

4. Install yarn
- Install yarn https://classic.yarnpkg.com/en/docs/install
$ npm install --global yarn
$ yarn -v

5. Install Truffle
$ yarn global add truffle

6. Init truffle project
$ truffle init

7. Explain directory structure of truffle project
/contracts
/migrations
/test
truffle-config.js

8. Compile truffle project
$ truffle compile

9. Open remix
- https://remix.ethereum.org/

10. Create file in remix named Helloworld.sol and place content in Helloworld.sol in remix editor

11. Explain how to compile and deploy in remix